d education. He/She will not have a problem getting into pretty much any uni (provided they get the marks of course). &#10;That is for high school though, if you are looking for a primary school then I'd go for a private one (South African curriculum) until grade 6, then I'd move them to a Cambridge school for grade 7 (Its called Pre-O), After Pre-O comes O level, then As level and A level. Each takes 1 year, unless you do As and A in 1 year. &#10;So lets say the child is 13 years old when you move them to Pre-O, 14 in O level, 15 in As level and 16 in A level. They are then ready for uni at age 17... A year before matriculants and they have a far superior education that is recognized in every country. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1007" language="en" documentId="4707" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="D34M0n7" date="08-02-2011 03:49 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://mybroadband.co.za/vb/showthread.php/302963-Public-school-or-private-school-for-your-kid/page3" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4707" notes="" title="Public school or private school for your kid?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="162"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="163" end="421"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="422" end="746"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="747" end="1007"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>